    <description>The Balloon Observation Platforms for Planetary Science (BOPPS) Infrared Camera (BIRC) was a multispectral infrared imager designed to operate in 8 wavelengths between 2.5 and 5.0 microns, with each spectral width being about 3% of the center wavelength and the astronomical R-band near 640 nm. BIRC was designed to measure the water and CO2 emissions from comets at 2.73 and 4.3 microns, respectively, as well as the water-related infrared absorption feature in asteroids and the Moon from about 2.5 to 3.2 microns.</description>
